profile_positions.description:
Julius Clinical is the Contract Research Organization (CRO) that manages global clinical drug trials.

My Responsibilities Include:
- Works closely with the Director of Scientific Networks;
- Working independently and as part of a team, with responsibility for supervising junior team
members;
- Create and maintain Gantt Charts, Reports and Action Plans;
- Create, maintain, and adjust budgets;
- Conducting primary and secondary research and performing quantitative and qualitative
analysis to identify key issues in the field, translating the data into meaningful insights and
communicating recommendations to improve the development of scientific networks;
- Providing assistance in scientific research and clinical trials for the scientific network
- Taking part in calls, leading and documenting the discussion;
- Assisting development and writing of proposals/sponsorship requests with senior support
